President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Tony D’Agostino as a Member of the Board of Directors of the Securities Investor Protection Corporation. D’Agostino is currently a Managing Director and COO at UBS Investment Bank. He previously worked at Wachovia Securities and served in the US Navy for 24 years. D’Agostino holds a B.G.S from the University of Kansas and an M.S. from the Naval Postgraduate School.

President Obama also announced his intent to nominate Janice Eberly as Assistant Secretary for Economic Policy at the Department of the Treasury. Eberly is currently a Professor of Finance at the Kellogg School of Management at Northwestern University. She has previously worked at the White House Council of Economic Advisors and is a Research Associate of the National Bureau of Economic Research. Eberly's research focuses on macroeconomics and finance. She holds a B.S. from the University of California, Davis, and a Ph.D. in Economics from M.I.T.